qas.question: What is the political capital city?
How many rainy days does it typically have?
A colder city like Lugo has how many days with frosts?
Its sunniest city, Pontevedra, gets how may hours of sunlight per year?

context: As an example, <a0_0>Santiago de Compostela<a0_0/>, the political capital city, has an average of <a1_0>129<a1_0/> rainy days and 1,362 millimetres (53.6 in) per year (with just 17 rainy days in the three summer months) and 2,101 sunlight hours per year, with just <a2_0>6<a2_0/> days with frosts per year. But the colder city of Lugo, to the east, has an average of 1,759 sunlight hours per year, 117 days with precipitations (> 1 mm) totalling 901.54 millimetres (35.5 in), and <a3_0>40<a3_0/> days with frosts per year. The more mountainous parts of the provinces of Ourense and Lugo receive significant snowfall during the winter months. The sunniest city is Pontevedra with <a4_0>2,223<a4_0/> sunny hours per year.
